# Bind-mount the workspace instead of copying it into a volume. Our build runs in
# a docker-in-docker container (host daemon) that writes into the real host
# checkout; in act's default copy mode the runner works on a separate volume copy,
# so build output (build/<arch>/...) never appears where upload-artifact globs.
# Bind mode makes the runner workspace the same host dir the build writes to, so
# `gh act` matches real CI (upload-artifact included).
--bind
